  overviewText="Full-mouth reconstruction is for patients who have experienced significant dental breakdown — from neglect, trauma, acid erosion, severe grinding, or simply years of accumulated problems that were never addressed. Unlike a cosmetic smile makeover, reconstruction addresses both health and aesthetics in a specific clinical sequence: infection and gum disease are resolved first, then structure is rebuilt through implants and crowns, and finally aesthetics are refined with veneers or other cosmetic work. Every step is planned before treatment begins so you understand the full roadmap from day one."
  overviewExtra="Full-mouth reconstruction cases at our Bayside practice typically serve patients from throughout Queens — Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, Little Neck, Flushing, and Douglaston — who need more comprehensive care than a single specialist can provide. At Thrive Dental, we coordinate the full scope of treatment in-house: our board-certified general dentists handle restorative and cosmetic work, and we work closely with our periodontist for gum and bone-related needs. This means fewer offices, better communication, and a more cohesive treatment plan. If you've been avoiding the dentist for years because of extensive dental problems and aren't sure where to start — start here. We'll assess the full picture and give you a clear, honest path forward."
